The port `3000` is hardcoded. Use an environment variable with a fallback:
```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```

### 7. 🟡 Static User Data Exposes PII
`/users` returns hardcoded email addresses. In a real app:
